{
    "VERSE": "45:25",
    "ARABIC": "\u0648\u064e\u0625\u0650\u0630\u064e\u0627 \u062a\u064f\u062a\u0652\u0644\u064e\u0649\u0670 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650\u0645\u0652 \u0621\u064e\u0627\u064a\u064e\u0670\u062a\u064f\u0646\u064e\u0627 \u0628\u064e\u064a\u0651\u0650\u0646\u064e\u0670\u062a\u064d \u0645\u0651\u064e\u0627 \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u062d\u064f\u062c\u0651\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0647\u064f\u0645\u0652 \u0625\u0650\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0653 \u0623\u064e\u0646 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064f\u0648\u0627\u06df \u0671\u0626\u0652\u062a\u064f\u0648\u0627\u06df \u0628\u0650\u0640\u0654\u064e\u0627\u0628\u064e\u0627\u0653\u0626\u0650\u0646\u064e\u0627\u0653 \u0625\u0650\u0646 \u0643\u064f\u0646\u062a\u064f\u0645\u0652 \u0635\u064e\u0670\u062f\u0650\u0642\u0650\u064a\u0646\u064e",
    "ENGLISH": {
        "TRANSLATION_0": "When Our Clear Signs are recited to them their only argument is to say, 'Bring us our fathers if you are telling the truth.'",
        "TRANSLATION_1": "When Our clear revelations are recited to them, their only argument is to say: \"Bring our ancestors back, if what you say is true.\"\n",
        "TRANSLATION_2": "And when Our Clear Signs are rehearsed to them, their only contention is: \u201cBring back to us our fathers if you are truthful.\u201d\n",
        "TRANSLATION_3": "When Our enlightening revelations are recited to them, their only argument against it is, \"Bring our forefathers back to life if what you say is true\".\n",
        "TRANSLATION_4": "And when Our clear verses are recited to them, their only argument is, \u201cBring back our forefathers, if you are truthful!\u201d\n",
        "TRANSLATION_5": "And when Our Clear Ayat are recited to them, their argument is no other than that they say: \"Bring back our (dead) fathers, if you are truthful!\"\n",
        "TRANSLATION_6": "And when Our clear communications are recited to them, their argument is no other than that they say: Bring our fathers (back) if you are truthful.\n",
        "TRANSLATION_7": "And when Our signs are recited to them, clear signs, their only argument is that they say, 'Bring us our fathers, if you speak truly.'\n",
        "TRANSLATION_8": "And when Our clear revelations are recited unto them their only argument is that they say: Bring (back) our fathers. then, if ye are truthful.\n",
        "TRANSLATION_9": "Whenever Our clear revelations are recited to them, their only argument is to say, \"Bring back to us our forefathers, if what you say be true.\"\n",
        "TRANSLATION_10": "And when Our manifest revelations are rehearsed Unto them, their argument is no other than that they say bring our fathers, if ye say sooth.\n",
        "TRANSLATION_11": "When Our manifest signs are recited to them, their only argument is to say, \u2018Bring our fathers back [to life], if you are truthful.\u2019\n",
        "TRANSLATION_12": "And when Our Clear Signs are rehearsed to them their argument is nothing but this: They say, \"Bring (back) our forefathers, if what ye say is true!\"\n",
        "TRANSLATION_13": "And when Our Clear Verses are recited to them, their argument is no other than that they say: \"Bring back our (dead) fathers, if you are truthful!\"\n",
        "TRANSLATION_14": "And when Our verses are recited to them, their only argument is: 'Bring our fathers back to us, if what you say is true'\n",
        "TRANSLATION_15": "When Our clarifying Verses are recited to them, their only argument is to say, \u201cBring back our ancestors, if you are truthful.\u201d\n",
        "TRANSLATION_16": "And when Our verses are recited to them as clear evidences, their argument is only that they say, \"Bring [back] our forefathers, if you should be truthful.\"\n",
        "TRANSLATION_17": "[45:25] And when Our signs, of the Qur\u2019\u0101n, indicating Our power to resurrect, are recited to them, being clear signs, evident [signs] (bayyin\u0101tin, \u2018clear signs\u2019, is a circumstantial qualifier), their only argument is to say, \u2018Bring us our fathers, alive, if you are being truthful\u2019, [when you say] that we will be resurrected.\n",
        "TRANSLATION_18": "(And when Our clear revelations) explaining the commands and prohibitions (are recited unto them) to Abu Jahl and his host (their only argument) and excuse to Muhammad (pbuh) (is that they say: Bring (back) our fathers then) do bring, Muhammad, our fathers back to life so that we may ask them whether what you say is true or false, (if ye are truthful) that we will be resurrected again after we die.\n"
    },
